  RR$ such that
  $ |{x in RR: tilde(g)(x) != tilde(f)(x)}| = 0. $
  Take $g = tilde(g)|_B$, then clearly $g$ is Borel measurable, and
  $ |{x in B: g(x) != f(x)}| <= |{x in RR: tilde(g)(x) != tilde(f)(x)}| = 0$.
]

