#solution[
  Clearly $chi^*_1([0,1]) <= 1$ for all $x in RR$, with equality at $x in (0,
  1)$. For $x <= 0$, we have:
  $ 1 / (2t) integral_(x-t)^(x+t) chi^*_([0,1]) = 1 / (2t) max{0, min{1, x+t}}, $
  for all $t > -x$.

  This quantity is equal to:
  $
    1 / (2t) min{1, x+t} = cases(0 "if" t < -x, 1/2 + x/(2t) "if" -x<=t <= 1-x,
  1/(2t) "otherwise").
  $

